title: Virgil_Introduction
---
Dante : "Have pity on me, whatever you may be, a shade, a man." #line:0fd5718 

Shade : "Not man; I once was man. Both of my parents came from Lombardy, and both claimed Mantua as native city. I was a poet, born under false and lying gods." #line:081e541 

Dante : "Could you be Virgil? The-" #line:06637f1  

Virgil : "We cannot talk now, the beasts will get to us, let's get moving!" #line:05e67b5 

